29/05/2005
ZVORNIK, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) police spokesman Radovan Pejic reiterated Friday (27 May) that entity police would arrest war crimes indictees Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic if accurate information about their whereabouts becomes available.
Visiting Zvornik, Pejic said RS police are undertaking activities daily related to implement the law on war crimes co-operation.
Also Friday, the Eastern Sarajevo Public Security Centre reported it had information that Mladic might be travelling in a military vehicle on the road between Sokolac and Vlasenica.
RS police stopped the car but did not find Mladic.
(RTRS, Fena - 27/05/05)
